nodes.title: Important
widgets_values:
Always start prompts with:
fcsks fxhks fhyks

nodes.title: ControlNet
widgets_values:
I always leave ControlNet on. 
If you don't want to use it, just set "strength" to zero.

Besides using it for the usual stuff like poses, you can use a low quality image of your subject and set the strength to like 0.5-0.8. 
It's useful for when you don't have high quality images.

nodes.title: Source Images
widgets_values: I usually get pretty good results with 5-12 images.

nodes.title: Important
widgets_values:
Depending on the checkpoint you want to use, don't forget to change the samplers, schedulers, steps and CFG for the samplers in the 1st pass group, face detailer and upscaler sampler.

Besides the recommended checkpoints in the hyperlora github (cyberrealistic, realvis, etc), I've had good results with BigLove and Lustify, with or without the DMD2 lora.

nodes.title: InstantID/HyperLoRA
widgets_values: play with the "cn_strength" (Apply InstantID Advanced node) and the "weight" (HyperLoRA Apply LoRA) values to see what works best for you.
